{{Infobox organization | name = Hackerspace.gr | bgcolor = <!-- header background color --> | fgcolor = <!-- header text color --> | image = Hackerspace.gr.svg | image_border = | size = 180px | alt = <!-- alt text; see [[WP:ALT]] --> | caption = Hackerspace.gr logo | map = <!-- optional --> | msize = <!-- map size, optional, default 250px --> | malt = <!-- map alt text --> | mcaption = <!-- optional --> | map2 = | abbreviation = | motto = | predecessor = | successor = | formation = 2011 | extinction = | type = [[Non-profit]] | status = | purpose = [[Hacker (computer security)|Hacking]] | headquarters = | location = [[Greece]] | coords = <!-- Coordinates of location using a coordinates template --> | region_served = | membership = | language = <!-- official languages --> | general = <!-- Secretary General --> | leader_title = Origin | leader_name = [[Athens]] | leader_title2 = Platforms | leader_name2 = | leader_title3 = Founders | leader_name3 = [[Evangelos Balaskas]], [[Pierros Papadeas]], [[Nikos Roussos]] | leader_title4 = Products | leader_name4 = | key_people = | main_organ = <!-- gral. assembly, board of directors, etc --> | parent_organization = <!-- if one --> | affiliations = | budget = | num_staff = | num_volunteers = | website = [http://www.hackerspace.gr Hackerspace.gr homepage] | remarks = | former name = }} '''Hackerspace.gr''' ('hsgr') is a [[hackerspace]] in [[Athens]], [[Greece]], established in 2011. It operates as a cultural center, computer laboratory and meeting place (with free wireless access).<ref>[http://vrypan.net/weblog/2011/09/25/6424/ Visit in Hackerspace.gr]</ref> Hackerspace.gr promotes [[creative coding]]<ref>[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=q549zJE8d84 Hackerspace.gr Creative Hacking]</ref> and hardware hacking<ref>[http://hackaday.com/2011/12/06/web-enabled-kinect/ Web-enabled Kinect]</ref> through its variety of activities.<ref>[http://hackerspace.gr/wiki/Vision_en hsgr Vision]</ref><ref>[http://www.linuxinside.gr/forum/hackerspacegr-%CF%83%CF%85%CE%BD%CE%AD%CE%BD%CF%84%CE%B5%CF%85%CE%BE%CE%B7-%CE%BC%CE%B5-%CF%84%CE%BF%CF%85%CF%82-%CE%B4%CE%B7%CE%BC%CE%B9%CE%BF%CF%85%CF%81%CE%B3%CE%BF%CF%8D%CF%82 hackerspace.gr interview with the founders]</ref> According to its website: "Hackerspace.gr is a physical space dedicated to creative code and hardware hacking, in Athens".
==Vision== Hackerspace.gr vision is inspired by the [[Open Source]] philosophy. The main values, according to its vision page, are Excellence, Sharing, Consensus, and Do-ocracy.<ref>[https://www.hackerspace.gr/wiki/Vision_en Hackerspace.gr Vision]</ref> It is a self-funded community, through a membership fee,<ref>[https://www.hackerspace.gr/wiki/People Hackerspace.gr Members list]</ref> individual donations and supporters.<ref>[https://www.hackerspace.gr/wiki/Supporters Hackerspace.gr supporters]</ref> Every year Hackerspace.gr publishes its annual financial balance titled "The cost of Hacking".<ref>[http://budget.hackerspace.gr/ The cost of Hacking]</ref>[[File:Hackerspace.gr.JPG|thumb|An overview of Hackerspace.gr main lab|left]]
==Events== It organizes workshops, lectures,<ref>[http://www.linuxinside.gr/content/hackfest7-%CF%83%CF%84%CE%BF-hackerspacegr-%CF%83%CF%84%CE%B7%CE%BD-%CE%B1%CE%B8%CE%AE%CE%BD%CE%B1 Hackfest7 in Hackerspace.gr in Athens]</ref> and entertainment<ref>[http://wiki.softwarefreedomday.org/2011/Greece/Athens/Hsgr Freedom Software Day in Greece]</ref> and informational <ref>[http://www.kala-nea.gr/archives/27320 linux Lessons for beginners]</ref> events. The events calendar lists several events weekly.<ref>[http://hackerspace.gr/wiki/Timeline hsgr Timeline]</ref> Furthermore, hackerspace.gr is open for visitors as long as any of the administrators is in the premises.
==Projects== Hackerspace.gr is an incubator place for many projects. Currently there is an [[OpenROV]] Taskforce on Hackerspace.gr.<ref>[http://openrov.com/profiles/blogs/openrov-across-the-sea OpenROV across the sea]</ref> Verese community, a project participating on [[Mozilla]] WebFWD,<ref>http://blog.webfwd.org/post/14465709140/webfwd-summit-report-our-teams-in-their-own-words</ref> is hosting its regular meetings at Hackerspace.gr. [[Ardupad]] was also incubated at Hackerspace.gr.<ref>[http://ardupad.cc/ Ardupad]</ref> A [[USB dead drop|USB drop]] is located in the central area of the hackerspace.<ref>[http://deaddrops.com/db/?page=view&id=850&PHPSESSID=jqa4faft0cmjeiuvk9cb28hg36 Hackerspace.gr Deadrop]</ref> A custom open hardware delta 3D printer design, Anadelta<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://github.com/hsgr/anadelta|title=hsgr/anadelta|website=GitHub|access-date=2016-11-08}}</ref> is developed to cover its members need for a large 3D printer.
== Services == Hackerspace provides several online services to its members, visitors, and the general public. In particular some of its members are running an instance of the [[etherpad]] lite collaborative editor,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://pad.hackerspace.gr|title=HSGR Pad|website=pad.hackerspace.gr|access-date=2016-11-08}}</ref> a [[Diaspora (social network)|diaspora]] pod <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://librenet.gr|title=diaspora* social network|last=Inc.|first=Diaspora,|website=librenet*|access-date=2016-11-08}}</ref> and a [[XMPP|Jabber/XMPP]] service.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://gnu.gr|title=gnu.gr jabber|website=gnu.gr|access-date=2016-11-08}}</ref> [[File:Hackerspace.gr Geodesic Dome by night.jpg|thumb|Hackerspace.gr mobile hackerspace deployed during an amateur astronomer camp in central Greece.]]
== Mobile Hackerspace == Hackerspace.gr usually deploys its geodesic dome in order to establish a mobile hackerspace when a large number of its members participate in events and venues that are away from its physical location providing tools, equipment and free of charge services for attendees. [[File:UPSat testing.jpg|left|thumb|UPSat testing in hackerspace.gr]]
== Libre Space Foundation == hackerspace.gr is utilized as the headquarters of [[Libre Space Foundation]], an open space technologies non-profit, as its laboratory and main working space. Libre Space Foundation shares its testing and manufacturing equipment with hackerspace.gr's users and visitors.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://satnogs.org/2015/02/new-lab-equipment/|title=New lab equipment|date=2015-02-23|newspaper=SatNOGS|language=en-US|access-date=2016-11-08}}</ref>
Libre Space Foundation has deployed<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://satnogs.org/2015/01/satnogs-1-in-athens-greece/|title=SatNOGS #1 in Athens, Greece|date=2015-01-06|newspaper=SatNOGS|language=en-US|access-date=2016-11-08}}</ref> its first [[SatNOGS]] ground station on the rooftop of hackerspace.gr and has used its machine, and electronics facilities for the manufacture, integration and initial testing of [[UPSat]] the first open source satellite, and also the first satellite made in Greece.
