'''Instytut Rozbitek''' is a center near [[Poznań]], [[Poland]] meant for development of new work in the areas of film, theatre, music and new media. The institute was founded by the Oscar - Winning Polish composer [[Jan A.P. Kaczmarek]] in 2004. The Institute consists of the 19th-century castle and surrounding buildings, which are currently under renovation.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://rozbitek.org/en/about-rozbitek|title=About Rozbitek|accessdate=15 October 2012}}</ref>

It is a place of workshops.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.europeanfilmacademy.org/2011-Rozbitek-Poland.198.0.html|title=Jam-Sessions in a Polish Castle|accessdate=15 October 2012}}</ref> In 2011 and 2012 it was one of the locations of the Master Classes workshops, during the Transatlantyk - Poznan International Film and Music Festival.
